  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2004-05-20",
    "date": "2004-07-14T20:15:09Z",
    "text": "Tax Code Termination Act - Mandates the termination of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 after December 31, 2009, except for self-employment taxes, Federal Insurance Contributions Act taxes, and Railroad Retirement taxes.\n\nDeclares that any new Federal tax system should be a simple and fair system that: (1) applies a low rate to all Americans; (2) provides tax relief for working Americans; (3) protects the rights of taxpayers and reduces tax collection abuses; (4) eliminates the bias against savings and investment; (5) promotes economic growth and job creation; and (6) does not penalize marriage or families.\n\nRequires that the new Federal tax system be approved by Congress in its final form by July 4, 2009."
  },
